ngineer of chevrolet and assistant chief engineer of buick mr runkle has a bachelor’s and master’s degree in mechanical engineering from the university of michigan and an mba from the massachusetts institute of technology as a sloan fellow back to top donald l runkle executive profile  biography  bloomberg july    pm et capital markets company overview of tennenbaum capital partners llc snapshotpeople  overviewboard memberscommittees executive profile donald l runkle operating executive and senior executive advisor tennenbaum capital partners llcagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationships background mr donald l runkle also known as don has been an operating executive of tennenbaum capital partners llc since  and serves as its senior executive advisor in this position mr runkle serves as chairman of eaglepicher corporation and serves on various other tennenbaum portfolio company boards mr runkle served as the chief executive officer at of ecomotors international inc from  to  he served as chief executive officer for four years since   he also runs a personal consulting business mr runkle served as the chief technology officer of dph holdings corp since january   until  and was responsible for global supply management manufacturing and engineering oversight research and development aftermarket the commercial vehicle accounts and the daimlerchrysler account he was also the leader for the daimlerchrysler and commercial vehicle customer teams mr runkle began his career as a coop student at eastman kodak and ford motor company following graduation he joined general motors in  where he held a variety of assignments including chief engineer of chevrolet chief engineer of powertrain and racing at the buick division director of advanced vehicle engineering vice president of gms advanced engineering staff and vice president of gms north american engineering center where he was gms top engineering executive from  to  he served as special advisor of asia automotive acquisition corp since june   mr runkle served as the president of delphi steering division since  where he led a significant turnaround and divestiture of uncompetitive assets he served as a vice president and president of delphi saginaw division from  to  he served as the president of delphi energy  engine management systems division from  to  from  to  he coled the ipo and spinoff of delphi from general motors mr runkle served as an executive vice president of delphi corporation from  to  with the responsibility for the dynamics  propulsion sector during his tenure at delphi he led many international acquisitions in  he joined delphi corporation where he coled the ipo process he is a member of the engineering advisory council for the university of michigan mr runkle has been the executive chairman of the board at ioxus inc since april   he serves as the chairman of autocam corporation he has been member of advisory board of general fusion inc since june  he has been a member of strategic advisory board of powergenix corporation since july  he served as a director of transonic combustion inc since may  via motors inc since january   he has been independent director of lear corp since november   he serves as a director on mits sloan school of management and james p womancks lean enterprise institute he serves as a member of technical advisory board at tula technology inc he serves as a director of wincup corp and environmental systems products holdings he serves as a member of advisory board of actacell inc he was the chairman of eaglepicher pharmaceutical services llc from  to  he served as a vice chairman of dph holdings corp since january   until  and served as its director since  as delphi vicechairman mr runkle was the senior executive for deploying lean principles streamlining and integrating engineering manufacturing and purchasing he served as executive chairman of ecomotors international inc since  he serves as a director of ecomotors international inc he served as chairman of the board of ep management corporation he served as a director of asia automotive acquisition corp since june   he was a board member of envirotest he has published numerous articles and papers and holds a patent for rotary engine mounting mr runkle is active in the society of automotive engineers and the society of manufacturing engineers mr runkle cofounded with the department of energy the united states advanced battery consortium usabc he is a life member of the shingo academy which recognizes distinguished manufacturing excellence a recipient of the wu manufacturing leadership award which identifies role models for visionary and strategic thinking manufacturing leaders shingo prize academy lifetime member for distinguished manufacturing excellence and a recipient of the asm medal for the advancement of research he is a recognized business leader and productprocess innovator mr runkle earned bachelors and masters degrees from the university of michigan in mechanical engineering mr runkle was also a sloan fellow and received his masters degree in business administrationmanagement science from the massachusetts institute of technologyread full background corporate headquarters  th streetsanta monica california united statesphone fax  board members memberships chairmaneaglepicher pharmaceutical services llcpresentindependent directorlear corporationpresentexecutive chairman of the boardioxus incpresentdirectorvia motors inc education masters degree massachusetts institute of technologymba massachusetts institute of technologybachelors degree university of michiganmasters degree university of michigan other affiliations lear corporationdph holdings corpep management corporationmassachusetts institute of technologyuniversity of michiganpowergenix corporationeaglepicher pharmaceutical services llcasia automotive acquisition corptransonic combustion i